OL,4,CCovid inquiry opens in Belfast
OL,6,FFormer first minister Baroness Arlene
OL,7,FFoster, current First Minister
OL,8,FMichelle O'Neill (who was deputy first
OL,9,Fminister during the pandemic), and
OL,10,FHealth Minister Robin Swann are
OL,11,Fexpected to be among those witnesses
OL,12,Fto give evidence.
OL,14,FKey figures in Stormont's Department
OL,15,Fof Health, including chief medical
OL,16,Fofficer Sir Michael McBride and chief
OL,17,Fscientific adviser Professor Ian
OL,18,FYoung, are also expected to face
OL,19,Fquestions at the inquiry.
